While verifying the "B vs D" TODO section (cell 26/27, tied to 琳达问题7/小雨问题5), I found a real math bug: the TODO instructed `dct_truncated @ B.T`, but the correct inverse for the batched row-vector convention `dct_ii` actually uses is `dct_truncated @ B` (no transpose) — confirmed numerically (6.09 dB vs a broken 35.28 dB that would have failed the assert). I fixed cell 27's TODO code/comments and rewrote cell 26's derivation to correctly distinguish the single-frame (left-multiply `D.T`) vs batched (right-multiply `D`) cases, explicitly answering "why right-multiply not left" and "B is literally D, not a variant."

